<div class="row-fluid-wrapper row-depth-1 row-number-1 ">
<div class="row-fluid ">
<div class="span12 widget-span widget-type-cell blog-inner-content" style="" data-widget-type="cell" data-x="0" data-w="12">

<div class="row-fluid-wrapper row-depth-2 row-number-1 ">
<div class="row-fluid ">
<div class="span12 widget-span widget-type-custom_widget " style="" data-widget-type="custom_widget" data-x="0" data-w="12">
<div id="hs_cos_wrapper_module_1523032069834331" class="hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module widget-type-blog_content" style="" data-hs-cos-general-type="widget" data-hs-cos-type="module">
    <div class="blog-section">
<div class="blog-post-wrapper cell-wrapper">
<div class="blog-section">
<div class="blog-post-wrapper cell-wrapper">
<div class="page-title">
<h1><span id="hs_cos_wrapper_name" class="hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_meta_field hs_cos_wrapper_type_text" style="" data-hs-cos-general-type="meta_field" data-hs-cos-type="text">Mattress size guide: Which size is right for you?</span></h1>
</div>
<div class="page-body">
<div class="post-date">
Jun 7, 2021 8:00:00 AM
</div>
<div class="post-body">
<span id="hs_cos_wrapper_post_body" class="hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_meta_field hs_cos_wrapper_type_rich_text" style="" data-hs-cos-general-type="meta_field" data-hs-cos-type="rich_text"><p><img src="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hubfs/Mattress%20sizes-jpg.jpeg" loading="lazy" alt="Mattress size guide"></p>
<p>When you’re shopping for a new mattress, choosing the right size is vital to ensuring you will be comfortable at night. You need to make sure you and anyone with whom you share a bed can stretch out comfortably.</p>
<!--more-->
<p>While we’ll be primarily discussing the length and width of your mattress, it’s also important to keep mattress height in mind. You want to make sure you can get in and out of bed comfortably. Many mattresses are quite thick, so you may want to consider a low-profile 5-inch box spring (compared to a standard 8-inch box spring) or bunk board to lower your total bed height by a few inches.</p>
<p>And no matter what size you’re considering, we highly recommend that you pair your new mattress with a new, flexing box spring and a <a href="https://www.originalmattress.com/heavy-duty-bed-frames" rel="noopener" target="_blank">heavy duty frame</a>.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<h2 style="font-size: 30px;"><strong>Twin Size Mattresses: 38 x 75 inches (±1.5 inches)<img src="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Twin-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=150&amp;name=Twin-Size-jpg.jpeg" loading="lazy" width="150" style="width: 150px; float: right;" alt="twin mattress dimensions" srcset="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Twin-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=75&amp;name=Twin-Size-jpg.jpeg 75w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Twin-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=150&amp;name=Twin-Size-jpg.jpeg 150w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Twin-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=225&amp;name=Twin-Size-jpg.jpeg 225w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Twin-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=300&amp;name=Twin-Size-jpg.jpeg 300w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Twin-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=375&amp;name=Twin-Size-jpg.jpeg 375w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Twin-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=450&amp;name=Twin-Size-jpg.jpeg 450w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px"></strong></h2>
<p>While twin-size beds are commonly used for children and teens, all of our twin-size mattresses provide adult-level support so they can be a great fit for anyone.</p>
<p><span><a href="https://www.originalmattress.com/twin">View all of our twin-size sets and mattresses here.</a></span></p>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<h2 style="font-size: 30px;"><strong>Twin XL </strong><strong>Size Mattresses</strong><strong>: 38 x 80 inches (±1.5 inches)<img src="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Twin-XL-jpg-1.jpeg?width=150&amp;height=277&amp;name=Twin-XL-jpg-1.jpeg" loading="lazy" width="150" style="width: 150px; float: right; height: auto; max-width: 100%;" alt="twin XL mattress dimensions" height="277" srcset="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Twin-XL-jpg-1.jpeg?width=75&amp;height=139&amp;name=Twin-XL-jpg-1.jpeg 75w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Twin-XL-jpg-1.jpeg?width=150&amp;height=277&amp;name=Twin-XL-jpg-1.jpeg 150w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Twin-XL-jpg-1.jpeg?width=225&amp;height=416&amp;name=Twin-XL-jpg-1.jpeg 225w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Twin-XL-jpg-1.jpeg?width=300&amp;height=554&amp;name=Twin-XL-jpg-1.jpeg 300w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Twin-XL-jpg-1.jpeg?width=375&amp;height=693&amp;name=Twin-XL-jpg-1.jpeg 375w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Twin-XL-jpg-1.jpeg?width=450&amp;height=831&amp;name=Twin-XL-jpg-1.jpeg 450w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px"></strong></h2>
<div><br>
<p>Twin XL beds are common in college dorms and apartments. They provide a bit of</p>
<p>&nbsp;extra length that can be valuable for adults.</p>
<p>If you put two twin XL mattresses together, it will equal a split king. This can be a great option for <span><a href="https://www.originalmattress.com/adjustable-beds">adjustable bases</a></span>, but it’s also an option for a couple that has different comfort preferences. If this is an option you choose, you’ll want to keep the thickness of each mattress in mind so that you don’t have a big difference in the surface height of each side. We do offer options like low-profile box spring<span>s</span> and bunk boards that may help address this issue.</p>
<p><span><a href="https://www.originalmattress.com/twin-xl">View all of our twin XL-size sets and mattresses here.</a></span></p>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<h2 style="font-size: 30px;"><strong>Full </strong><strong>Size Mattresses</strong><strong>: 53 x 75 inches (±1.5 inches)<img src="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Full-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=150&amp;height=175&amp;name=Full-Size-jpg.jpeg" loading="lazy" width="150" style="width: 150px; float: right; height: auto; max-width: 100%;" alt="full mattress dimensions" height="175" srcset="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Full-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=75&amp;height=88&amp;name=Full-Size-jpg.jpeg 75w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Full-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=150&amp;height=175&amp;name=Full-Size-jpg.jpeg 150w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Full-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=225&amp;height=263&amp;name=Full-Size-jpg.jpeg 225w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Full-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=300&amp;height=350&amp;name=Full-Size-jpg.jpeg 300w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Full-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=375&amp;height=438&amp;name=Full-Size-jpg.jpeg 375w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Full-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=450&amp;height=525&amp;name=Full-Size-jpg.jpeg 450w" sizes="(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px"></strong></h2>
<p>A full size is a great option for single sleepers who want a little extra room or couples who may not have space in their room for a queen or king.</p>
<p>We highly recommend you use a heavy-duty frame that features a center rail with a foot that touches the floor for support.</p>
<p>For full-size sets, you can choose a split box spring which can make transport and set up easier in houses and apartments with tight hallways, stairways, and doorways. You can also request that we hinge your mattress so that it can be folded in half from head to foot in either direction for easier transport (see image below for reference).</p>
<p><span><a href="https://www.originalmattress.com/full">View all of our full-size sets and mattresses here.</a></span></p>
<p><strong> <img src="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hubfs/Orthopedic_SPT_King_Delivery_5260%20(2)-jpg.jpeg" loading="lazy" alt="folded King Size mattress"></strong></p>
<h2 style="font-size: 30px;"><strong>Full XL Size Mattresses: 53 x 80 inches (±1.5 inches)<img src="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Full-XL-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=200&amp;height=233&amp;name=Full-XL-Size-jpg.jpeg" loading="lazy" width="200" style="width: 200px; float: right; height: auto; max-width: 100%;" alt="full XL mattress dimensions" height="233" srcset="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Full-XL-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=100&amp;height=117&amp;name=Full-XL-Size-jpg.jpeg 100w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Full-XL-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=200&amp;height=233&amp;name=Full-XL-Size-jpg.jpeg 200w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Full-XL-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=300&amp;height=350&amp;name=Full-XL-Size-jpg.jpeg 300w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Full-XL-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=400&amp;height=466&amp;name=Full-XL-Size-jpg.jpeg 400w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Full-XL-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=500&amp;height=583&amp;name=Full-XL-Size-jpg.jpeg 500w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Full-XL-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=600&amp;height=699&amp;name=Full-XL-Size-jpg.jpeg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px"></strong></h2>
<p>Like twin XL, a full XL bed provide<span>s</span> a bit of extra length that can be valuable for adults.</p>
<p>We highly recommend you use a heavy-duty frame that features a center rail with a foot that touches the floor for support.</p>
<p>For full XL-size sets, you can choose a split box spring which can make transport and set up easier in houses and apartments with tight hallways, stairways, and doorways. You can also request that we hinge your mattress so that it can be folded in half from head to foot in either direction for easier transport.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span><a href="https://www.originalmattress.com/full-xl">View all of our full XL-size sets and mattresses here.</a></span></p>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<h2 style="font-size: 30px;"><strong>Queen Size Mattresses: 60 x 80 inches (±1.5 inches)<img src="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Queen-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=200&amp;height=233&amp;name=Queen-Size-jpg.jpeg" loading="lazy" width="200" style="width: 200px; float: right; height: auto; max-width: 100%;" alt="queen mattress dimensions" height="233" srcset="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Queen-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=100&amp;height=117&amp;name=Queen-Size-jpg.jpeg 100w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Queen-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=200&amp;height=233&amp;name=Queen-Size-jpg.jpeg 200w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Queen-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=300&amp;height=350&amp;name=Queen-Size-jpg.jpeg 300w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Queen-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=400&amp;height=466&amp;name=Queen-Size-jpg.jpeg 400w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Queen-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=500&amp;height=583&amp;name=Queen-Size-jpg.jpeg 500w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Queen-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=600&amp;height=699&amp;name=Queen-Size-jpg.jpeg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px"></strong></h2>
<p>The queen is the most common bed size as it offers plenty of room for two adults to comfortably sleep without taking up too much space in a smaller bedroom.</p>
<p>We highly recommend you use a heavy-duty frame that features a center rail with a foot that touches the floor for support.</p>
<p>For <a href="/the-ultimate-guide-to-queen-mattress-sizes-everything-you-need-to-know" rel="noopener" target="_blank">queen-size mattress</a> sets, you can choose a split box spring which can make transport and set up easier in houses and apartments with tight hallways, stairways, and doorways. You can also request that we hinge your mattress so that it can be folded in half from head to foot in either direction for easier transport.</p>
<p><span><a href="https://www.originalmattress.com/queen"></a></span></p><div class="hs-cta-embed hs-cta-simple-placeholder hs-cta-embed-182350297371" style="max-width:100%; max-height:100%; width:210px;height:60.78125px" data-hubspot-wrapper-cta-id="182350297371"><a href="https://www.originalmattress.com/queen">
</a><a href="/hs/cta/wi/redirect?encryptedPayload=AVxigLIT1S0y1guSbhu49Xr2fHPmKadgJdKztydb9fnJa5E0Hl7UFY939dGnm75wsF3EezSaEeluQ9cghLv4sBFtisAN7onZSeCP%2BPREu8oRbvZwb7drcuX1txYCCmoS19%2BlmKa8KaX5qYNRkUH3csLdCn02V6isAsS0DhfdXSr4H%2By7ysHb9Ljbp9mB&amp;webInteractiveContentId=182350297371&amp;portalId=6058680" target="_blank" rel="noopener" crossorigin="anonymous">
<img alt="Shop Queen Size Mattresses" loading="lazy" src="https://no-cache.hubspot.com/cta/default/6058680/interactive-182350297371.png" style="height: 100%; width: 100%; object-fit: fill" onerror="this.style.display='none'">
</a>
</div>
<p></p>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<h2><span style="font-size: 30px;"><strong>King Size Mattresses: 76 x 80 inches (±1.5 inches)<img src="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/King-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=200&amp;height=233&amp;name=King-Size-jpg.jpeg" loading="lazy" width="200" style="width: 200px; float: right; height: auto; max-width: 100%;" alt="king mattress dimensions" height="233" srcset="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/King-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=100&amp;height=117&amp;name=King-Size-jpg.jpeg 100w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/King-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=200&amp;height=233&amp;name=King-Size-jpg.jpeg 200w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/King-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=300&amp;height=350&amp;name=King-Size-jpg.jpeg 300w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/King-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=400&amp;height=466&amp;name=King-Size-jpg.jpeg 400w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/King-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=500&amp;height=583&amp;name=King-Size-jpg.jpeg 500w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/King-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=600&amp;height=699&amp;name=King-Size-jpg.jpeg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px"> </strong></span></h2>
<p>The king mattress is the largest standard size, providing plenty of room for two adults to stretch out and get comfortable — all with some extra space to accommodate a child or pet.</p>
<p>We highly recommend you pair your new mattress with a real working box spring, as well as a heavy-duty frame that features a center rail with a foot that touches the floor for support.</p>
<p>All of our king-size mattresses come standard with a hinge that allows them to be folded in half from head to foot in either direction. King-size sets also come standard with split box springs.</p>
<p><span><a href="https://www.originalmattress.com/king">View all of our king-size sets and mattresses here.</a></span></p>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<h2><span style="font-size: 30px;"><strong>California King Size Mattresses: 72 x 84 inches (±1.5 inches)<img src="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Cal-King-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=250&amp;name=Cal-King-Size-jpg.jpeg" loading="lazy" width="250" style="width: 250px; float: right;" alt="california king mattress dimensions" srcset="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Cal-King-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=125&amp;name=Cal-King-Size-jpg.jpeg 125w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Cal-King-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=250&amp;name=Cal-King-Size-jpg.jpeg 250w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Cal-King-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=375&amp;name=Cal-King-Size-jpg.jpeg 375w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Cal-King-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=500&amp;name=Cal-King-Size-jpg.jpeg 500w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Cal-King-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=625&amp;name=Cal-King-Size-jpg.jpeg 625w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Cal-King-Size-jpg.jpeg?width=750&amp;name=Cal-King-Size-jpg.jpeg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 250px) 100vw, 250px"> </strong></span></h2>
<p>Many people believe that California king is the largest mattress size, but it actually has a smaller total area than a king. However, it does provide a bit of extra length which can be great for those sleepers who are taller than average.</p>
<p>We highly recommend you pair your new mattress with a real working box spring, as well as a heavy-duty frame that features a center rail with a foot that touches the floor for support.</p>
<p>All of our California king-size mattresses come standard with a hinge that allows them to be folded in half from head to foot in either direction. California king-size sets also come standard with split box springs.</p>
<p><span><a href="https://www.originalmattress.com/california-king">View all of our California king-size mattresses and sets here.</a></span></p>
<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
<h2><span style="font-size: 30px;"><strong>Common custom size mattresses<img src="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/82629565_2988721327828066_1792431689620783104_n-jpg.jpeg?width=250&amp;name=82629565_2988721327828066_1792431689620783104_n-jpg.jpeg" loading="lazy" style="float: right; width: 250px;" width="250" alt="original mattress factory custom mattress" srcset="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/82629565_2988721327828066_1792431689620783104_n-jpg.jpeg?width=125&amp;name=82629565_2988721327828066_1792431689620783104_n-jpg.jpeg 125w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/82629565_2988721327828066_1792431689620783104_n-jpg.jpeg?width=250&amp;name=82629565_2988721327828066_1792431689620783104_n-jpg.jpeg 250w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/82629565_2988721327828066_1792431689620783104_n-jpg.jpeg?width=375&amp;name=82629565_2988721327828066_1792431689620783104_n-jpg.jpeg 375w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/82629565_2988721327828066_1792431689620783104_n-jpg.jpeg?width=500&amp;name=82629565_2988721327828066_1792431689620783104_n-jpg.jpeg 500w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/82629565_2988721327828066_1792431689620783104_n-jpg.jpeg?width=625&amp;name=82629565_2988721327828066_1792431689620783104_n-jpg.jpeg 625w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/82629565_2988721327828066_1792431689620783104_n-jpg.jpeg?width=750&amp;name=82629565_2988721327828066_1792431689620783104_n-jpg.jpeg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 250px) 100vw, 250px"> </strong></span></h2>
<p>At The Original Mattress Factory, we can also make <a href="https://www.originalmattress.com/custom-size" rel="noopener" target="_blank">custom-size mattresses and box springs</a> for everything from antique beds, RVs, boats, and more. We can also offer corner cuts and hinging to make sure your custom mattress is a perfect fit. Some common custom sizes include:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<h3>California queen: 60 x 84 inches</h3>
</li>
<li>
<h3>Super single*: 46.5 x 81 inches</h3>
</li>
<li>
<h3>Three-quarter: 48 x 75 inches</h3>
</li>
<li>
<h3>Three-quarter short: 48 x 72 inches</h3>
</li>
<li>
<h3>RV queen: 60 x74 inches</h3>
</li>
</ul>
<p>Length and width dimensions for custom size mattresses and box springs have a tolerance of ± 1.5 inches.</p>
<img src="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Boat%20Mattress%2003-jpg.jpeg?width=250&amp;name=Boat%20Mattress%2003-jpg.jpeg" loading="lazy" width="250" style="width: 250px; float: right;" alt="original mattress factory custom boat mattress" srcset="https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Boat%20Mattress%2003-jpg.jpeg?width=125&amp;name=Boat%20Mattress%2003-jpg.jpeg 125w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Boat%20Mattress%2003-jpg.jpeg?width=250&amp;name=Boat%20Mattress%2003-jpg.jpeg 250w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Boat%20Mattress%2003-jpg.jpeg?width=375&amp;name=Boat%20Mattress%2003-jpg.jpeg 375w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Boat%20Mattress%2003-jpg.jpeg?width=500&amp;name=Boat%20Mattress%2003-jpg.jpeg 500w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Boat%20Mattress%2003-jpg.jpeg?width=625&amp;name=Boat%20Mattress%2003-jpg.jpeg 625w, https://blog.originalmattress.com/hs-fs/hubfs/Boat%20Mattress%2003-jpg.jpeg?width=750&amp;name=Boat%20Mattress%2003-jpg.jpeg 750w" sizes="(max-width: 250px) 100vw, 250px"></div>
<div><br>
<p>Please note that while we will make just about any size you request, you may have trouble finding sheets and other bedding to fit your custom mattress and box spring. There are catalogs that sell many special size sheets. You may also buy a flat sheet for a size larger than your custom mattress and tuck it under.</p>
<p style="font-size: 12px;">* A standard super single is approximately 48 x 84 inches. At The Original Mattress Factory, our super single finishes at approximately 46.5 x 81 inches, with a tolerance of ± 1.5 inches. This smaller size makes is easier to put on sheets and make the bed.</p>
<p>Ready to get started? These orders are a bit more complex, so we want to take some time to walk you through your options. You can <span><a href="https://www.originalmattress.com/find-a-store">contact your nearest OMF store</a></span> or reach out via <span><a href="mailto:info@originalmattress.com">info@originalmattress.com</a></span> and we’ll put you in touch with the right team.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><em>Ready to start your mattress buying journey? Come to The Original Mattress Factory first. No one knows more than our team about what makes a great mattress great. Whether you buy from us or not, you’ll be better prepared to make a smart mattress buying decision.&nbsp;<span><a href="https://www.originalmattress.com/find-a-store">Find a store near you.</a></span></em></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
